    funFact: { en: 'The "Dunning-Kruger effect" shows that people with the least competence in a skill tend to overestimate their ability the most, while experts tend to underestimate theirs. The less you know, the more confident you feel!', ka: 'The "Dunning-Kruger effect" shows that people with the least competence in a skill tend to overestimate their ability the most, while experts tend to underestimate theirs. The less you know, the more confident you feel!', ru: 'The "Dunning-Kruger effect" shows that people with the least competence in a skill tend to overestimate their ability the most, while experts tend to underestimate theirs. The less you know, the more confident you feel!', hy: 'The "Dunning-Kruger effect" shows that people with the least competence in a skill tend to overestimate their ability the most, while experts tend to underestimate theirs. The less you know, the more confident you feel!' },
